Frontier correctness review — eight defects identified:

Defect 1 [LOAD-BEARING — source-fidelity-loss recurrence]: Goose's draft
asserts canonical paths are /Users/admin/Library/Logs/iap/<name>.{out,err}.log
and presents this as "verified by StandardOutPath and StandardErrorPath in
both reference plists." The actual source plists do NOT use those paths:
- com.iap.platform-registry.plist writes to /Users/admin/.platform-registry/launchd.{stdout,stderr}.log
- com.iap.arr-apikey-sweep.plist writes to /Users/admin/.platform-logs/arr-apikey-sweep.launchd.log
The canonical iap/ paths are produced by the migration script's normalization
pass (lines 52-53 of d-17-51-migrate-to-launchdaemons.sh: d['StandardOutPath']=f'{LOG_DIR}/{label}.out.log'),
not by the source plists. Goose conflated source-plist values with
post-migration values and presented the inferred result as source-verified.
Same shape as Session 7's fabricated AppRole defect: plausible-shape
autocomplete from training data when source files contained the actual
values. Watchlist failure mode N=3 confirmed (Sessions 5, 7, 8).

Defect 2: Heartbeat naming convention ambiguous. Goose used <name>.heartbeat
without distinguishing whether <name> is the full label (com.iap.foo) or
the short form (foo). The verify script (lines 27-38) and arr-apikey-sweep.plist
line 11 both use the short form (label minus com.iap. prefix). Frontier
clarified to <short>.heartbeat with explicit definition.

Defect 3: Bootstrap-step-count framing inconsistency. Header said "five
commands" but body has six numbered steps; migration script's per-job
bootstrap loop (lines 84-87) has four launchctl operations (bootout,
bootstrap, enable, kickstart). Steps 1-2 of the per-job form (cp, chown/chmod)
mirror the script's pre-loop pass (lines 68-73). Frontier removed the
"five commands" framing and described the per-job sequence as 6 steps,
4 of which are launchctl operations.

Defect 4: RunAtLoad declared as uniformly required. com.iap.platform-registry.plist
includes RunAtLoad=true; com.iap.arr-apikey-sweep.plist omits it. Frontier
noted the asymmetry and described when each is appropriate.

Defect 5: UserName=admin / GroupName=staff declared as plist-author fields.
Both source plists OMIT these fields. They are applied at install time by
the migration script (lines 44-45: d['UserName']='admin'; d['GroupName']='staff').
Frontier corrected to: do not author these in the source plist; the migration
script is the single owner.

Defect 6: [UNVERIFIED] flag preserved on a resolvable fact. Goose flagged
check-repo-coherence.py expectations as UNVERIFIED. The legacy launchd-jobs.md
§5/§7 documents the mechanism, and the script's LAUNCHD_RECENCY_EXPECTATIONS
dict (line 76) is directly readable. Frontier replaced with verified text
showing the dict structure and the LAUNCHD_RECENCY_EXEMPT_LABELS pattern.

